items.name: TGL Psy
items.description:
A rather dark-psy inspired model (over)trained on 200+ AI Generated training images and a custom set of AI Generated regularization images, for a total of 23K steps.
The model was trained on images generated with SD 1.5 using the following artists and artstyles as sole prompts.

Pablo Picasso, Alex Grey, Zdzisław Beksiński, Katsuhiro Otomo, H.P. Lovecraft, Clive Barker, M. C. Escher, H.R. Giger, Yves Tanguy, Andy Warhol, Jackson Pollock, Frida Kahlo, Marcel Duchamp, Salvador Dalí, Georgia O'Keeffe, Yayoi Kusama, Jean-Michel Basquiat, Ai Weiwei, Dadaism, Fluxus, Surrealism, Abstract Expressionism, Pop Art, Outsider Art, Neo-Dada, Street Art/Graffiti, Installation Art, Performance Art, Biomechanical, Soviet Propaganda

Even the regularization images are AI generated interpretations of those artists/art styles!

Use this model if you want to get surprises. Even just prompting for the class and keywords (`artstyle bse`) will get you quite some results.

It cannot do faces, hands very well. You can get lucky (see example shots), but it is not the purpose of the model anyway.

I strongly suggest using this model when you want to get very artsy, psy, otherworldly.

I did a lot of experiments with this model and all its intermediaries (I saved each 5k steps during the dreambooth training) and found that it works best with the following settings:

Positive prompt:

artstyle bse ((YOUR TOPIC GOES HERE)), best quality, masterpiece, ultra high res, (photorealistic:1.4), raw photo, sharp focus, HDR, detailed skin
Negative Prompt

Anime, cartoon, ng_deepnegative_v1_75t, (badhandv4:1.2), (worst quality:2), (low quality:2), (normal quality:2), lowres, bad anatomy, bad hands, normal quality, (monochrome), (grayscale), watermark
Resolution:

512^2

Sampling method

DDIM

You can also get interesting results with larger resolutions like 1200x900, by increasing the steps massively, although not useful for subjects, it can be interesting for "backgrounds"

Resources:
I used both badhandv4 (https://civitai.com/models/16993/badhandv4-animeillustdiffusion) and ng_deepnegative_v1_75 (https://civitai.com/models/4629/deep-negative-v1x) in almost all prompts.

PS:
you will notice that the prompts in all pictures say the model used is baked. That is because I dumbass renamed the model after I downloaded it from my SD online instance and after I generated all tons of images with it. As I had named it baked in the SD instance, that is what the images meta data tell too. However, the model used to generate those image is the current uploaded TGL Psy model, you can verify this by simply recreating the images.

items.name: Character | Lucifer – ObeyMe
items.description:
Recommended parameters:

推荐参数：

Clip skip: 2

weight:0.4~1

Sampler: DPM++ SDE Karras | DPM++ 2M Karras

Steps: 25

Size: 512x512|512x768|768x512

CFG Scale: 7

 

————

Instructions:

1.Fan art, please do not use for commercial purposes.

2.In addition to the default trigger "luci\(obeyme\)", it's recommended to add another prompt "red eyes".

3.Common 2D base models can be used, but the art style generated may not vary significantly (overfitting). For pastel style, it's suggested to increase the weight. So far, it hasn't been successful in generating a good-looking thickly painted style (perhaps controlnet could be used to achieve it).

It is not recommended to use 3D base models.

Realistic base models can be used and will default to an Asian face.

4.Proficient in drawing portraits and upper body, but not skilled at drawing full body (if you insist on trying, please be mentally prepared).

5.If you want more variation in the art style, it is recommended to use "lora block weight" to decrease the weight of the background and pose.

6.If you want a stable output of costumes, it is recommended to set the "lora" weight to 0.9-1, without using layered weights. Increase the weight of the corresponding costume trigger words in the prompt. The focus should be on the costume, not the pose or composition. Lower the resolution and generate multiple images in one run, as there will be hits eventually. You can also try describing the clothing in the prompt, but be cautious as the base model might be influenced.

The following table shows the trigger for costumes.

https://docs.google.com/document/d/1JQjzlG6iV7vu0amfOMsqxzPDDt6MShSH6XDoC29NnQg/edit?usp=sharing

说明：

1.  同人作品，请勿商用。

2.  触发词除了默认的luci\(obeyme\)，最好再加一个red eyes。

3.  常用的二次元底模都可以跑，但跑出来的画风不会差太多（过拟合了），粉彩类的建议提高权重，目前没成功跑出过好看的厚涂风（也许需要借助controlnet来实现）。

不建议使用3d类底模。

现实类底模可以用，会默认出亚洲脸。

4.  擅长画肖像和半身，完全不擅长画全身（非要尝试的话请先做好心理准备）。

5.  想要画风差异大一点，建议使用lora block weight降低背景、动作权重。

6.  如果想要服装稳定出，建议lora权重在0.9~1，不使用分层权重，prompt里提高对应服装触发词的权重，不强求动作和构图，分辨率调低一点一次多跑几张，总有命中的。也可以尝试描述衣服的prompt，但容易被底模污染。

以下表格是服装的触发词。

items.name: 一种廉价滤镜/A kind of cheap beauty filter
items.description:
效果对比图仍在审核中/The effect comparison chart is still under review

————

一种廉价的滤镜效果。

这类模型不太会做，这只是个学习中的产物。

具体效果因参数和模型而异。

推荐强度1~1.3。

适合写实模型，动漫模型没有测试。简单测试后的效果：为画面进一步添加轮廓。但不明显，附带的将亮度提升或者是为写实增加一点动漫风格。

制作写实图片可以尝试一下，如果质量不好就不要用了，正如我说的，这只是个学习过程的产物，我也仅仅试了三组参数而已。

————

A cheap filter effect.

This type of model is not very good at making, it is just a product of learning.

The specific effect varies depending on the parameters and model.

Recommended strength 1-1.3

Suitable for realistic models, anime models have not been tested. The effect after simple testing: further adding contours to the screen. But it's not obvious, as it comes with increasing brightness or adding a bit of anime style to realism.

You can try creating realistic images, but if the quality is not good, don't use them. As I said, this is just a product of the learning process, and I have only tried three sets of parameters.

items.name: Chewbacca from "Star Wars"
items.description:
Chewbacca, nicknamed "Chewie", is a fictional character in the Star Wars franchise. He is a Wookiee, a tall, hirsute, bipedal, intelligent species originating from the fictional planet of Kashyyyk. Chewbacca is the loyal friend and first mate of Han Solo, and serves as co-pilot on Solo's spaceship, the Millennium Falcon; together they help the Rebel Alliance defeat the Galactic Empire and restore freedom to the galaxy.

This model is trained with SFW sources only. If you get NSFW content, what's wrong with you??

Please provide constructive criticism.

You can support me here to be able to render better models (https://ko-fi.com/djo226). Supporters can request model.

Prompt : Chewbacca, photography, trending on artstation, sharp focus, studio photo, intricate details, highly detailed, by greg rutkowski <lora:Chewbacca:0.4>

Negative prompt: (deformed iris, deformed pupils, semi-realistic, cgi, 3d, render, sketch, cartoon, drawing, anime, mutated hands and fingers:1.4), (deformed, distorted, disfigured:1.3), poorly drawn, bad anatomy, wrong anatomy, extra limb, missing limb, floating limbs, disconnected limbs, mutation, mutated, ugly, disgusting, amputation

Steps: 90, Sampler: DPM++ 2M Karras, CFG scale: 12, Seed: -1, Face restoration: GFPGAN, Size: 768x1024, Model hash: 81086e2b3f, Model: realisticVisionV20_v20

Face restoration is optional, may provide better result if not activated.

Use Chewbacca as trigger.

You may have to go at a low ratio like <lora:Chewbacca:0.3> to get want you want.

items.name: Power Anime Screencap Style Character LoRA
items.description:
Please read the description below!

This is an experimental Character LoRA that was trained with only anime screencaps in training data on a new specific model that could be used to emulate specific anime styles, with the use of supplementary Anime Style models.

This is not a generic character model, even though it could in theory be used as one.

I will release a generic Power Character LoRA trained on AnyLora soon to compare the results, so stick around for that :) (Both models contain the same screencaps, but the other one also uses fanart images in training dataset)

Big thanks to Lykon (https://civitai.com/user/Lykon) for making this possible!

To achieve similar results as showcased, it is necessary to follow a few simple steps:

  • Use AnyLoRA Anime Mix Screencap Style Model to generate images (https://civitai.com/models/84586/aam-anylora-anime-mix-anime-screencap-style-model).

  • Use Chainsaw Man Anime Style Lora (https://civitai.com/models/53149/chainsaw-man-anime-style-lora) with the weight of 0.4-0.6.

  • Pay attention to removing certain tags that may disrupt the style (CGI, photorealistic, RAW photo, e.t.c.)

  • Recommended weight for this LoRA: 0.7-0.85

  • Activation word for this LoRA: PowerScreencap

  • Use of " beautiful detailed eyes, ", or other eye enhancement LoRA's is not recommended for this Character LoRA.

  • Use of "Detail Tweaker LoRA" model is recommended for better details.

  • Upscale to 1.5.

  • I haven't received the same quality of results using other anime SD checkpoints, but if you want to use it as a generic character LoRA make sure to lower the weights.


I would appreciate any reviews, positive or negative!

I would very much appreciate you sharing your results ^_^

If you have any suggestions on what LoRA i should do next, please share them in the comments

Enjoy :)

items.name: Tai Chi punk
items.description:
Tai Chi Punk LORA (Large OpenAI Reinforcement Artistry) model is an innovative art generation model designed to blend elements of Tai Chi, girlhood, cyberpunk, and sci-fi light to inspire and enhance artistic creations. Built upon the trained realGoofball_v10 base model, it possesses remarkable artistic creativity and innovative thinking.

Inspired by the grace and balance of Tai Chi, the innocence and delicacy of girlhood, the avant-garde aesthetics of cyberpunk, and the mysterious ambiance of sci-fi light, Tai Chi Punk LORA model generates unique and imaginative art pieces by skillfully merging these elements together.

With the use of professional art vocabulary and technical terms, the model excels in producing breathtaking visual effects. It adeptly captures the fluidity and dynamism of Tai Chi, the elegant postures and soft lines of girlhood, the mechanical elements and avant-garde style of cyberpunk, as well as the dazzling effects and enigmatic atmosphere of sci-fi light.

I don't know if it works with realistic models, nor I know if it should. (I'm still learning!) The same applies to nsfw.

Feedback is appreciated.

items.name: FF16 Kazuya Takahashi Style
items.description:
Trained this LoRA to welcome FF16‘s incoming release: )

2D base model is recommended for this Kazuya Takahashi (FF16 concept art) style:

  • Anything/Counterfeit/GhostMix

Recommended configuration:

  1. Use trigger word Kazuya Takahashi, concept art to trigger the style.

  2. 0.8-1 weight (0.9 is mostly recommended to avoid details off )

  3. Do Not check Restore Faces

  4. If eyes are off or too rough, try to add eye details to improve

  5. Not limited to character art, animals/creatures like summoning beasts are also supported in this style, e.g. add wolf, dragon, phoenix, etc to the prompt

Please kindly leave your comments and rating on this model. Thank you!
